<TITLE> 'Devdas' novel inspires new film </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MUMBAI, Oct 18 (bdnews24.com/Reuters)  'Devdas', a classic Indian novella about unrequited love which has been filmed many times over in several Indian languages, is being remade once again, this time setting its characters in the present. 'Dev D' is about a rich boy and his transition from self-pity to self-discovery. "We have set the incidents and characters of the original Devdas in contemporary times but have retained the intrinsic essence of the novel," said Anurag Kashyap, the director and writer of the film. "It is a film about the youth of the country and how the present generation is living their lives by experimenting with it," he added. The original novella was written in Bengali in the early 20th century by Sarat Chandra Chatterjee. The film is expected to open in 20
